Islanders' Capuano Is Made Full-Time Coach After Serving on Interim Basis

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-04-12T14:44:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/islanders-capuano-is-made-full-time-coach-after-serving-on-interim-basis.html
Jack Capuano was named coach of the
New York Islanders today with the National Hockey League team
removing the interim label from his job.  Capuano took over the team in November and led the
Islanders to a 26-29-10 record, including 15-12-6 after the All-
Star break.  The move was announced in a news release from the team.
